article.headline: Michigan 83, Norfolk St. 49
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. -- Manny Harris scored 16 points to lead five Michigan double-figure scorers on Tuesday as the Wolverines cruised to an 83-49 victory against Norfolk State. Michigan improved to 4-1. Norfolk State, playing its third of four straight road games, fell to 1-2. Anthony Wright finished with 12 points for Michigan. DeShawn Sims and Jevohn Shepherd had 11 apiece and freshman Zack Novak added a season-high 10. Michael Deloach led the Spartans with 15 points. Michigan missed its first 10 shots before Stu Douglass hit a three-point basket with 15:21 remaining in the first half. Norfolk State missed its first eight field goal attempts and didn't get its first basket until the 6:42 mark of the first half. The Wolverines led 38-23 at halftime. A 27-4 spurt that began early in the second half increased Michigan's lead to 69-31 with just under nine minutes left in the game.
